## <a id='ert'></a> Pivotal Application Service (PAS) Highlights

### <a id='blobstore-authentication'></a> Support for AWS IAM Instance Profiles

Operators can now configure PAS to use AWS IAM Instance Profiles for S3 authentication.

### <a id='blobstore-encryption'></a> Support for S3 Server-Side Encryption with AWS KMS

Operators can now configure PAS to use server-side encryption with AWS Key Management Service (KMS) for S3 blobstore.

### <a id='route-consistency'></a> Improved Resiliency and Consistency for App Routes

Gorouter now uses TLS to verify app identity by default.
For more information about how Gorouter uses app instance validation to keep its routing table current,
see [Routing to App Instances](https://docs.pivotal.io/pivotalcf/2-1/concepts/http-routing.html#apps).

### <a id='hsts-haproxy'></a> HSTS Support for HAProxy

You can now enable HTTP Strict Transport Security (HSTS) for HAProxy.

### <a id='container-metrics'></a> Container Metrics Included in Syslog Drains

Container metrics can now be delivered in create-user-provided-service (CUPS) Syslog Drain bindings.

